ate forcing by carbonaceous and sulfate aerosols (1998) Clim. Dyn., 14, pp. 839-851; Rao, A.K., Sperber, K.R., Simulation of El Niño Southern Oscillation: Results from the coupled model intercomparison project (2002) Clim. Dyn., 19, pp. 191-209; Rayner, N.A., Horton, E.B., Parker, D.E., Folland, C.K., Hackett, R.B., Version 2.2 of the global sea-ice and sea surface temperature dataset, 1903-94 (1996) Climate Research Technical Note, 74. , Hadley Centre, U.K. Meteorological Office; Ricard, J.-L., Royer, J.-F., A statistical cloud scheme for use in a AGCM (1993) Ann. Geophys., 11, pp. 1095-1115; Royer, J.F., Cariolle, D., Chuavin, F., De'que', M., Douville, H., Hu, R.M., Planton, S., Valcke, S., Simulation of climate change during 21st century including stratospheric ozone (2002) C. R. Geoscience, 334, pp. 147-154; Rupa Kumar, K., Pant, G.B., Parthasarathy, B., Sontakke, N.A., Spatial and subseasonal patterns of the long-term trends of Indian summer monsoon rainfall (1992) Int. J. Climatol., 12, pp. 257-268; Rupa Kumar, K., Ashrit, R.G., Regional aspects of global climate change simulations: Validation and assessment of climate response over Indian monsoon region to transient increase of greenhouse gases and sulfate aerosols (2001) Mausam, Special Issue on Climate Change, 52 (1), pp. 229-244; Salas Mélia, D., A global coupled sea ice-ocean model (2002) Ocean Modelling, 4, pp. 137-172; Stephenson, D.B., Douville, H., Rupa Kumar, K., Searching for a fingerprint of global warming in the Asian summer monsoon (2001) Mausam, 52, pp. 213-220; Terray, L., Thual, O., Belamari, S., Déqué, M., Dandin, P., Delecluse, P., Levy, C., Climatology and interannual variability simulated by the ARPEGE-OPA coupled model (1995) Clim. Dyn., 11, pp. 487-505; Timbal, B., Mahfouf, J.-K., Royer, J.-F., Cariolle, D., Sensitivity to prescribed changes in sea surface temperature and sea ice in doubled carbon dioxide experiments (1995) Clim. Dyn., 12, pp. 1-12; Timmerman, A., Oberhuber, J., Bacher,